name: axios
text:
Lawmakers and other leading figures are paying tribute to Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg, who died tonight at age 87.

Chief Justice John Roberts: “Our Nation has lost a jurist of historic stature...a tireless and resolute champion of justice.”
https://t.co/vOPnl8uAOB

name: axios
text:
Chuck Schumer: "Tonight, we mourn the passing of a giant in American history, a champion for justice, a trailblazer for women. She would want us all to fight as hard as we can to preserve her legacy."
https://t.co/vOPnl8uAOB

name: axios
text:
Lindsey Graham: "It was with great sadness that I learned of the passing of Justice Ginsburg. Justice Ginsburg was a trailblazer who possessed tremendous passion for her causes. She served with honor and distinction as a member of the Supreme Court."
https://t.co/vOPnl8uAOB

name: axios
text:
NEW: Trump will move within days to nominate his third Supreme Court justice in just three-plus years — and shape the court for decades to come, top Republican sources tell Axios.
https://t.co/dLxQRkr7RF

name: axios
text:
McConnell and GOP senators are ready to move to confirm a nominee before Election Day, setting up one of the most consequential periods of our lifetimes, the sources say.

"Oh, we'd fill it,” he said last year on what he'd do if a justice died in 2020.
https://t.co/dLxQRkr7RF

name: axios
text:
NEW: Mitch McConnell has released a statement following the death of Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg: "President Trump’s nominee will receive a vote on the floor of the United States Senate."
https://t.co/dLxQRkr7RF

name: axios
text:
Last week, Trump released a revamped list of potential Supreme Court justices that included 20 new names, including Sens. Tom Cotton and Ted Cruz.

Judge Amy Coney Barrett is also still at the top of the list.
https://t.co/twP9L2t9r7

name: axios
text:
When he talks about Russia, Joe Biden has sounded like Ronald Reagan all summer, setting up a potential Day 1 confrontation with Vladimir Putin if he wins in November.
https://t.co/PXT6EpHD9H

name: axios
text:
NEW: Trump said Supreme Court Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg "led an amazing life," after he finished a campaign rally in Bemidji, Minnesota, and learned of her death.

https://t.co/y6IpLiyBjw
